<subSubSection pageId="46" pageNumber="325" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="46.[1387,2594,2655,3239]" pageId="46" pageNumber="325">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1389,1736,3131,3160]" pageId="46" pageNumber="325">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List (as 
<taxonomicName box="[2482,2593,3131,3160]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="46" pageNumber="325" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Microtus</taxonomicName>
clarke). Clarke's Vole is not uncommon and perhaps is even locally abundant.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
